 Swiftie or not?=E2=80=9D I don=E2=80=99t know what the line is, but there =
is some line where you have to declare yourself as a Swiftie, and that come=
s with certain responsibilities, or you have to know enough. It=E2=80=99s i=
nteresting that she has replicated, you know that thing you were saying abo=
ut the Wall Street Journal article? You know how a lot of stereotypes of te=
ch people is that they call everything content, and they treat it as a disp=
osable commodity, that=E2=80=99s a critique of a lot of artists that I know=
. And the funny thing is, there=E2=80=99s actually a lot of truth to it. I =
don=E2=80=99t know about the content thing, because it=E2=80=99s hard to ju=
st come up with a word to describe all that stuff. But there is a way in wh=
ich most technology platforms do structurally want, as businesses, to treat=
 all content as a commodity. That=E2=80=99s just a more favorable model.

*Commoditize your complements.*

*EW:* Yeah, exactly. And one of the things about tech that I find interesti=
ng is you look over the full era of the Internet era now, and you have thes=
e tech giants who are constantly trying to commoditize their complements in=
 every way, because they all make money in some other form and that probabl=
y has had a net at some big level, a way of destroying a lot of profits jus=
t across the board, and a lot of content businesses. So I think what tech p=
eople didn=E2=80=99t appreciate about Taylor was as a savvy business woman =
she was like, look, this is my living and I have to find a way to avoid thi=
s spiral, and I=E2=80=99m going to experiment until I do. It may come in on=
e form or another form, it doesn=E2=80=99t matter ultimately, but I have to=
 find a way to create that feeling.

So, yes, the Taylor=E2=80=99s Version in listening to those tracks on Spoti=
fy instead of the original versions is a ritual. All strong communities hav=
e some hurdle to entry, that is just a minor one. It=E2=80=99s like, =E2=80=
=9CLook, all you have to do is click this one instead of that one=E2=80=9D.=
 If you had a playlist, swap all the tracks out, that=E2=80=99s a demonstra=
tion of loyalty, and it does. We know, it=E2=80=99s terrible to say, but we=
 know that humans do respond to those forms of community-building. It=E2=80=
=99s a time-tested way. If you go through some hurdle, you=E2=80=99re going=
 to feel =E2=80=94 let=E2=80=99s say why people get hazed when they go into=
